tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE experimental_data (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experimental_condition VARCHAR(255),
    data_type VARCHAR(50),
    data_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE experimental_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  data_name VARCHAR(255),
  data_type VARCHAR(50),
  experiment_date DATE,
  data_value FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE computational_models (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  model_name VARCHAR(255),
  model_type VARCHAR(50),
  author_name VARCHAR(100),
  publication_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE ExperimentalData (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    data_description TEXT,
    data_value FLOAT,
    experiment_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE ComputationalModel (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    model_description TEXT,
    model_file BYTEA,
    created_date TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE SystemBiologyResearch (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    research_title VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL,
    researcher_name VARCHAR(150) NOT NULL,
    research_description TEXT,
    research_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE research_projects (
  project_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  project_name VARCHAR(255),
  project_description TEXT,
  project_start_date DATE,
  project_end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE experimental_data (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_name VARCHAR(255),
  data_type VARCHAR(100),
  data_value FLOAT,
  experiment_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE computational_model (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  model_name VARCHAR(255),
  model_type VARCHAR(100),
  model_description TEXT,
  created_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE experimental_metadata (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT,
  metadata_key VARCHAR(100),
  metadata_value TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE model_parameters (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  model_id INT,
  parameter_name VARCHAR(100),
  parameter_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE model_output (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  model_id INT,
  output_name VARCHAR(100),
  output_value FLOAT
)
